    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop Internal Market Bill, enabling Government to break international law",
        "additional_details": "Britain is a founder of international law, how can we expect other countries to follow it if we don't ourselves?\r\n\r\nThe tabling of this bill has provoked outrage from two former PMs and caused two of the Government's most senior legal advisors to quit in protest.\r\n \r\nThese warnings should be heeded.\r\n \r\nThis Government signed the current agreement into law in full knowledge of the situation and cannot break the law now because it is 'politically convenient'.\r\n \r\nThere is a procedure to make amendments to the agreement in a committee with the EU, this Government should follow that, not break international law to get its way.",
        "background": "The UK Government is pursuing legislation which would enable it to break international law by overruling an international agreement signed with the EU. This is unprecedented. It will forever damage the UKs international reputation.",
